00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:13.000
Steak Sandwich with Caramelized Onions

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:14.300
Serves: 2

00:00:14.300 --> 00:00:15.400
Ingredients

00:00:15.400 --> 00:00:17.500
1 beef steak

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:22.600
1 tbsp Serjella extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for drizzling

00:00:22.600 --> 00:00:25.000
1 small cibatta bread loaf

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:26.700
A handful rocket leaves

00:00:26.700 --> 00:00:29.000
Salt and black pepper to taste

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:30.400
Ingredients for the caramelized onion

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:34.600
1 large onion, thinly sliced

00:00:34.600 --> 00:00:37.700
1 tsp Serjella extra virgin olive oil

00:00:37.700 --> 00:00:39.500
1 tsp butter

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:41.400
1 tsp sugar

00:00:41.400 --> 00:00:43.500
1 tsp balsamic vinegar

00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:45.400
¼ tsp salt

00:00:45.400 --> 00:00:48.100
Directions for the caramelized onion

00:00:48.100 --> 00:00:55.000
Heat the olive oil and butter in a pan and sauté the onion until soft

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:01.500
Add the salt, sugar and balsamic vinegar and continue cooking until brown

00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:02.400
Directions for the steak

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:07.800
Season the steak with salt and pepper on both sides

00:01:07.800 --> 00:01:14.800
Heat the olive oil in a pan and cook the steak for 2 minutes on each side.

00:01:14.800 --> 00:01:24.000
Leave the steak to rest for 2-3 minutes then slice thinly.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:27.500
Cut the ciabatta bread in half lengthways

00:01:27.500 --> 00:01:36.900
brush with a little olive oil and grill for 10 minutes in a preheated oven at 200°C

00:01:36.900 --> 00:01:38.300
Assemble the sandwich

00:01:38.300 --> 00:01:47.200
Spread the onions on one half of the bread then top with the meat and the rocket leaves

00:01:47.200 --> 00:01:53.000
Cover with the second half of the bread then cut the sandwich in half.

